            <h2>3.1 HTML / HTTP Protocol</h2>
            <h3>Who</h3>
            <p>Tim Berners-Lee, a British computer scientist, invented the World Wide Web. He developed core technologies like HTML and HTTP.</p>

            <h3>What</h3>
            <p>HTML (Hypertext Markup Language) structures web pages, while HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) facilitates communication between web browsers and servers.</p>

            <h3>Why</h3>
            <p>These technologies were created to make sharing information on the internet easier and more accessible.</p>

            <h3>When</h3>
            <p>Berners-Lee developed the first versions of HTML and HTTP between 1989 and 1990. The first website went live in 1991.</p>

